The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, August 26, 2004 				 Maiden Sah Petro flotation in pipeline
 A STAFF REPORTER				 	 Sah Petro chief Rajendra Sah (left) with MD Vivek Sah in Calcutta on Wednesday. Picture by Kishor Roy Chowdhury																								Calcutta, Aug. 25: Sah Petroleums Limited is set to enter the capital market with an initial public offering of Rs 31.78 crore.																								The proceeds from the issue will be used for the expansion and modernisation of existing plants at Vasai and Daman, to set up more branches and to meet additional working capital requirements.																								The company is the producer of a wide range of specialty industrial lubricants, rubber processing oils, greases, automotive lubes and various grades of other oils. The industrial lubricants constitute around 90 per cent of the companys total sales volume.																								The Indian lubricant market with an estimated consumption of more than 1.4 million tonnes has an industry turnover of over Rs 7,500 crore, of which automotive constitutes 60 per cent while industrial lubricants constitutes 40 per cent. 																								At present, we occupy around 5 per cent of the lubricants market in India. But our focus is on higher efficiency industrial products and we plan to reach a benchmark in the field before venturing aggressively into the automotive lubricants segment, said Vivek Sah, managing director of Sah Petroleums. 																								The production capacity for industrial oils at the existing plants is 40,000 tonnes and, with the proceeds from the issue, the capacity shall be expanded to 80,000 tonnes by April 2006. As on the closing of last fiscal, the company registered sales worth Rs 27,000 crore for industrial oils.																								For fiscal 2003-04, the company recorded a profit after tax of Rs 8.04 crore, a growth of 228 per cent from Rs 2.45 crore in the previous year. The turnover of the company increased to Rs 72.3 crore, a growth of 32 per cent from Rs 54.89 crore the previous year. 																								The IPO is opening on August 30 and is for 90,80,000 shares of Rs 5 each at a premium of Rs 30 per share. The issue will close on September 6. Post IPO, the promoters stake will be 54.6 per cent.
